43class RTCPReceiver final {
44 public:
45 class ModuleRtpRtcp {
46 public:
47 virtual void SetTmmbn(std::vector<rtcp::TmmbItem> bounding_set) = 0;
48 virtual void OnRequestSendReport() = 0;
49 virtual void OnReceivedNack(
50 const std::vector<uint16_t>& nack_sequence_numbers) = 0;
51 virtual void OnReceivedRtcpReportBlocks(
52 const ReportBlockList& report_blocks) = 0;
53
54 protected:
55 virtual ~ModuleRtpRtcp() = default;
56 };
57
58 RTCPReceiver(const RtpRtcpInterface::Configuration& config,
59 ModuleRtpRtcp* owner);
60 ~RTCPReceiver();
61
62 void IncomingPacket(const uint8_t* packet, size_t packet_size) {
63 IncomingPacket(rtc::MakeArrayView(packet, packet_size));
64 }
65 void IncomingPacket(rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> packet);
66
67 int64_t LastReceivedReportBlockMs() const;
68
69 void SetRemoteSSRC(uint32_t ssrc);
70 uint32_t RemoteSSRC() const;
71
72 // Get received NTP.
73 // The types for the arguments below derive from the specification:
74 // - `remote_sender_packet_count`: `RTCSentRtpStreamStats.packetsSent` [1]
75 // - `remote_sender_octet_count`: `RTCSentRtpStreamStats.bytesSent` [1]
76 // - `remote_sender_reports_count`:
77 // `RTCRemoteOutboundRtpStreamStats.reportsSent` [2]
78 // [1] https://www.w3.org/TR/webrtc-stats/#remoteoutboundrtpstats-dict*
79 // [2] https://www.w3.org/TR/webrtc-stats/#dom-rtcsentrtpstreamstats
80 bool NTP(uint32_t* received_ntp_secs,
81 uint32_t* received_ntp_frac,
82 uint32_t* rtcp_arrival_time_secs,
83 uint32_t* rtcp_arrival_time_frac,
84 uint32_t* rtcp_timestamp,
85 uint32_t* remote_sender_packet_count,
86 uint64_t* remote_sender_octet_count,
87 uint64_t* remote_sender_reports_count) const;
88
89 std::vector<rtcp::ReceiveTimeInfo> ConsumeReceivedXrReferenceTimeInfo();
90
91 // Get rtt.
92 int32_t RTT(uint32_t remote_ssrc,
93 int64_t* last_rtt_ms,
94 int64_t* avg_rtt_ms,
95 int64_t* min_rtt_ms,
96 int64_t* max_rtt_ms) const;
97
98 bool GetAndResetXrRrRtt(int64_t* rtt_ms);
99
100 // Called once per second on the worker thread to do rtt calculations.
101 // Returns an optional rtt value if one is available.
102 absl::optional<TimeDelta> OnPeriodicRttUpdate(Timestamp newer_than,
103 bool sending);
104
105 // A snapshot of Report Blocks with additional data of interest to statistics.
106 // Within this list, the sender-source SSRC pair is unique and per-pair the
107 // ReportBlockData represents the latest Report Block that was received for
108 // that pair.
109 std::vector<ReportBlockData> GetLatestReportBlockData() const;
110
111 // Returns true if we haven't received an RTCP RR for several RTCP
112 // intervals, but only triggers true once.
113 bool RtcpRrTimeout();
114
115 // Returns true if we haven't received an RTCP RR telling the receive side
116 // has not received RTP packets for too long, i.e. extended highest sequence
117 // number hasn't increased for several RTCP intervals. The function only
118 // returns true once until a new RR is received.
119 bool RtcpRrSequenceNumberTimeout();
120
121 std::vector<rtcp::TmmbItem> TmmbrReceived();
122 // Return true if new bandwidth should be set.
123 bool UpdateTmmbrTimers();
124 std::vector<rtcp::TmmbItem> BoundingSet(bool* tmmbr_owner);
125 // Set new bandwidth and notify remote clients about it.
126 void NotifyTmmbrUpdated();
127
128 private:
129 // A lightweight inlined set of local SSRCs.
130 class RegisteredSsrcs {
131 public:
132 static constexpr size_t kMaxSsrcs = 3;
133 // Initializes the set of registered local SSRCS by extracting them from the
134 // provided `config`.
135 explicit RegisteredSsrcs(const RtpRtcpInterface::Configuration& config);
136
137 // Indicates if `ssrc` is in the set of registered local SSRCs.
138 bool contains(uint32_t ssrc) const {
139 return absl::c_linear_search(ssrcs_, ssrc);
140 }
141
142 private:
143 absl::InlinedVector<uint32_t, kMaxSsrcs> ssrcs_;
144 };
145
146 struct PacketInformation;
147
148 // Structure for handing TMMBR and TMMBN rtcp messages (RFC5104,
149 // section 3.5.4).
150 struct TmmbrInformation {
151 struct TimedTmmbrItem {
152 rtcp::TmmbItem tmmbr_item;
153 int64_t last_updated_ms;
154 };
155
156 int64_t last_time_received_ms = 0;
157
158 bool ready_for_delete = false;
159
160 std::vector<rtcp::TmmbItem> tmmbn;
161 std::map<uint32_t, TimedTmmbrItem> tmmbr;
162 };
163
164 // Structure for storing received RRTR RTCP messages (RFC3611, section 4.4).
165 struct RrtrInformation {
166 RrtrInformation(uint32_t ssrc,
167 uint32_t received_remote_mid_ntp_time,
168 uint32_t local_receive_mid_ntp_time)
169 : ssrc(ssrc),
170 received_remote_mid_ntp_time(received_remote_mid_ntp_time),
171 local_receive_mid_ntp_time(local_receive_mid_ntp_time) {}
172
173 uint32_t ssrc;
174 // Received NTP timestamp in compact representation.
175 uint32_t received_remote_mid_ntp_time;
176 // NTP time when the report was received in compact representation.
177 uint32_t local_receive_mid_ntp_time;
178 };
179
180 struct LastFirStatus {
181 LastFirStatus(int64_t now_ms, uint8_t sequence_number)
182 : request_ms(now_ms), sequence_number(sequence_number) {}
183 int64_t request_ms;
184 uint8_t sequence_number;
185 };
186
187 // TODO(boivie): `ReportBlockDataMap` and `ReportBlockMap` should be converted
188 // to std::unordered_map, but as there are too many tests that assume a
189 // specific order, it's not easily done.
190
191 // RTCP report blocks mapped by remote SSRC.
192 using ReportBlockDataMap = std::map<uint32_t, ReportBlockData>;
193 // RTCP report blocks map mapped by source SSRC.
194 using ReportBlockMap = std::map<uint32_t, ReportBlockDataMap>;

303 mutable Mutex rtcp_receiver_lock_;

305
306 // Received sender report.
307 NtpTime remote_sender_ntp_time_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(rtcp_receiver_lock_);
308 uint32_t remote_sender_rtp_time_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(rtcp_receiver_lock_);
309 // When did we receive the last send report.
310 NtpTime last_received_sr_ntp_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(rtcp_receiver_lock_);

312 uint64_t remote_sender_octet_count_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(rtcp_receiver_lock_);
313 uint64_t remote_sender_reports_count_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(rtcp_receiver_lock_);
314
315 // Received RRTR information in ascending receive time order.
316 std::list<RrtrInformation> received_rrtrs_
317 RTC_GUARDED_BY(rtcp_receiver_lock_);
318 // Received RRTR information mapped by remote ssrc.
319 std::unordered_map<uint32_t, std::list<RrtrInformation>::iterator>
320 received_rrtrs_ssrc_it_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(rtcp_receiver_lock_);
321
322 // Estimated rtt, zero when there is no valid estimate.
323 const bool xr_rrtr_status_;
324 int64_t xr_rr_rtt_ms_;
325
326 int64_t oldest_tmmbr_info_ms_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(rtcp_receiver_lock_);
327 // Mapped by remote ssrc.
328 std::unordered_map<uint32_t, TmmbrInformation> tmmbr_infos_
329 RTC_GUARDED_BY(rtcp_receiver_lock_);
330
331 ReportBlockMap received_report_blocks_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(rtcp_receiver_lock_);
332 std::unordered_map<uint32_t, LastFirStatus> last_fir_
333 RTC_GUARDED_BY(rtcp_receiver_lock_);
334
335 // The last time we received an RTCP Report block for this module.
336 Timestamp last_received_rb_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(rtcp_receiver_lock_) =
337 Timestamp::PlusInfinity();
338
339 // The time we last received an RTCP RR telling we have successfully
340 // delivered RTP packet to the remote side.
341 Timestamp last_increased_sequence_number_ = Timestamp::PlusInfinity();
342
343 RtcpCnameCallback* const cname_callback_;
344 ReportBlockDataObserver* const report_block_data_observer_;
345

348
349 RtcpNackStats nack_stats_;
350
351 size_t num_skipped_packets_;
352 int64_t last_skipped_packets_warning_ms_;
